FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1771963515
OL,3,CBus drivers continue 10-day walkout on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FShe said: "We will not move if they
OL,7,Fdon't come back with anything. This
OL,8,Fwill take as long as it takes, and
OL,9,Fthey ain't moving."
OL,11,FThe strike started on Saturday 21
OL,12,FFebruary and is scheduled to last
OL,13,Funtil Tuesday 3 March.
OL,15,F"Strike is a last resort. We have been
OL,16,Ftrying to have constructive dialogue
OL,17,Fwith many many years. There's some of
OL,18,Four members who've worked for a long
OL,19,Fperiod of time.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1771963515
OL,3,CBus drivers continue 10-day walkout on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,F"There's (other) people out there who
OL,7,Fare getting much more pay, and they're
OL,8,Fgoing to start losing the very good,
OL,9,Fexperienced, skilled workers, because
OL,10,Fthey've had enough."
OL,12,FIn a statement, a spokesperson from
OL,13,Fthe Isle of Man Government said it
OL,14,F'must ensure good value on behalf of
OL,15,Fthe tax paying public, whilst ensuring
OL,16,Ffair salary is on offer to bus
OL,17,Fdrivers.'
OL,19,FDrivers had recently 'received a 3%
OL,20,Fpay increase', adding that 'the
OL,21,Faverage driver earns #36,000 per year'.
OL,26,@nD@JpmnD@Ppn
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
